org.apache.taverna.reference

Interface IdentifiedList<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<T>, Identified, Iterable<T>, List<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IdentifiedArrayList, T2ReferenceListImpl

    public interface IdentifiedList<T>
extends List<T>, Identified
    An identified list is a list which is identified by a T2Reference. Lists are immutable once named - if getId() returns a non null value all list methods modifying the underlying list data will throw IllegalStateException. In the reference management API this list sub-interface is used to represent both collections of identifiers (i.e. 'raw' stored lists) and more fully resolved structures where the types in the list can be reference sets, error documents and other lists of such. The ListDao interface uses only the 'raw' form consisting of flat lists of identifiers.

    The IdentifiedList has a unique T2Reference associated with it. If this is null the contents of the list may be modified, otherwise all modification operations throw IllegalStateException. Lists in T2, once named, are immutable.

    Author:
    Tom Oinn
